    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've implemented every widgets with connector using only the docs and I made a list of mistakes in the docs that I can easily fix before release:\r\n\r\n* connectCurrentRefinedValues\r\n    * doc type of `refinements` rendering option\r\n* connectHierarchicalMenu  \r\n    * typo for `attributes` in documentation of widget option\r\n    * `showParentLevel` wrong type\r\n* connectNumericRefinementList\r\n    * Example uses item.label and docs says use item.name\r\n    * No docs about operator widget params\r\n* connectNumericSelector\r\n    * Default operator is not displayed correctly in doc\r\n    * Add the possible operator options\r\n* connectPriceRanges\r\n    * Missing items.url doc\r\n\r\nBUT, all the code example of connectors are written in ES5. We should rewrite all connectors examples with ES6, it’s too hard to read when the code is a bit complex. What do you think?",
    "created_at": "2017-06-01T15:16:44Z",
